title: Script for letter for impeachment of Donald Trump
description:
This is not a meeting.

This is a script you can use to send your congressman/woman an email, letter or fax demanding the impeachment of Donald Trump.

Copy and paste into your word processor or browser.


[Your Name]
 [Your Address]
 [City, State, ZIP Code]
 [Email Address]
 [Date]

The Honorable [Senator’s Full Name]
 [Office Address]
 United States Senate
 Washington, D.C. 20510

Dear Senator [Last Name],

I am writing to express my deep concern regarding the ongoing actions of former President Donald J. Trump during his second term in office. I urge you to take immediate and decisive steps to initiate impeachment proceedings due to what I believe to be egregious violations of the Constitution and a blatant disregard for the rule of law.

Most alarming are his repeated attempts to undermine the authority of the federal judiciary by ignoring multiple court orders, including one from the Supreme Court which resulted in a 9-0 ruling to return Abrego Garcia to the United States when he was wrongfully deported to a concentration/death camp in El Salvador. This defiance erodes the foundational principle of checks and balances, setting a dangerous precedent for the executive branch to operate above the law. Such actions are not only unconstitutional, but also a direct threat to the democratic institutions that protect our freedoms.

Even more disturbing are recent reports and credible allegations that Mr. Trump has discussed or threatened to send American citizens to detention facilities abroad — specifically in El Salvador — without due process. This notion evokes the darkest chapters in modern history and represents an unacceptable abuse of power that should never be tolerated in a free society.

Impeachment is not a step to be taken lightly, but the gravity of these actions demands accountability. No individual, regardless of position or popularity, is above the law. The integrity of our democracy depends on the courage of our elected officials to uphold the Constitution and defend the rights of all citizens.

As your constituent, I implore you to lead with principle and act in the interest of justice and constitutional order. I urge you to support — or introduce — articles of impeachment and ensure a thorough investigation into these deeply troubling developments.

Thank you for your time, and for your service to our state and country. I look forward to your response and to seeing you stand on the right side of history.

Sincerely,
 [Your Name]

A working mom of two young daughters, Rebecca served in the Navy for over a decade as a helicopter pilot and aircraft commander. While in the service, she earned her M.B.A., with honors, from the University of Pennsylvania’s Wharton School of Business, and started her family. She’s always been driven by public service, a commitment to helping others, and a mission-first mindset—from serving in the Navy to driving innovation in healthcare. Those same values now fuel her campaign to represent the people of the 7th District. 

Especially in a time when so many people are feeling uncertainty, fear, or apathy about our political system, she believes that it is critical for a new generation of leaders to step forward and do the work needed to solve problems and support the middle class. She’s running for Congress to fulfill that mission! 

I can’t wait for you to personally meet her.  It’s my hope that you will feel the same enthusiasm I did towards everything she brings to this race. title: Power Move: CLICK TO CALL Your Legislator to Protect SNAP, WIC, and Head Start. TAKE ACTION NOW
description:
# Power Move: CLICK TO CALL Your Legislator to Protect SNAP, WIC, and Head Start. TAKE ACTION NOW.

## 📞 Congress is preparing budget cuts that threaten our communities. Use your power. Call now.

Proposed cuts to **SNAP**, **WIC**, and **Head Start** would devastate families—gutting food programs, maternal healthcare, and early childhood education.

These are survival programs. If we don’t act now, millions will lose access to care, nourishment, and the support they need to thrive.

This is your moment to use your voice—and your power.

---

## ✔ What’s at Stake

- **SNAP** helps feed **38+ million people** every month  
  ➤ [USDA SNAP Overview](https://www.fns.usda.gov/snap/supplemental-nutrition-assistance-program)

- **WIC** provides nutrition and health care for **6.6 million women, infants, and children**  
  ➤ [USDA WIC Program](https://www.fns.usda.gov/wic)

- **Head Start** supports **over 1 million children** through meals, mental health, and early learning  
  ➤ [Head Start Facts](https://eclkc.ohs.acf.hhs.gov/about-us/article/head-start-program-facts)

---

## 📣 How to Take Action

✅ **Step 1: Call your Representative and both U.S. Senators**

You have **three federal lawmakers**—your House Representative and two Senators. Call all three.

Need to find them?

- 🏛️ [Look up your Representative (House)](https://www.house.gov/representatives/find-your-representative)  
- 🏛️ [Look up your Senators (Senate)](https://www.senate.gov/senators/senators-contact.htm)

✅ **Step 2: Review the script below** or write your own message

✅ **Step 3: Click the button on this page** to be auto-connected to their office  
(No phone number needed—we’ll dial for you.)

---

## ☎️ Sample Call Script

> Hi, my name is \_\_\_\_ and I’m a constituent from \_\_\_\_ (ZIP code).  
>
> I’m calling to urge you to **fully fund SNAP, WIC, and Head Start** in the federal budget.  
>
> - SNAP helps feed **38+ million people** each month  
> - WIC supports **6.6 million mothers and children** with nutrition and care  
> - Head Start provides early learning and support to **1+ million children**  
>
> These programs helped me [insert your personal story, or why this matters to your family, church, or community].  
>
> Please protect these programs. I’ll be calling each week until I know they’re fully funded.  
>
> Thank you.

---

## 🧭 What Happens When You Call

You’ll first reach a **real operator at the U.S. Capitol Switchboard**.

- Say: “Connect me to [Senator or Representative NAME]”  
- They’ll transfer you directly to their D.C. office  
- If the line is busy or you get voicemail, **leave a message**—it still gets logged

Have your **ZIP code and story ready**—and don’t be afraid to speak from the heart.

---

## 🔁 Keep the Pressure On

✔ Call every week until the vote is done  
✔ Ask 3 friends to call too  
✔ Flood their phone lines—they can’t ignore us

Justice has a League. And you have the power to act.

title: 5/7 Stop Elon Musk Rally!
description:
Join Indivisible Greater Vancouver (IGV) and MoveOn Clark County for a peaceful protest at Vancouver's Tesla dealership! 

Unvetted DOGE operatives hired by Musk are accessing our data, impounding funds allocated by Congress, and crippling federal agencies. This empowers the surveillance state and paves the way for billionaire tax cuts, deregulation and more. 

We'll march on the sidewalk/right of way outside Vancouver's Tesla showroom on Fourth Plain Blvd., staying on public property. Park on the street or in the surrounding neighborhood - not in business parking lots. Bring a large sign to let everyone know we stand united against Musk, DOGE, and unelected oligarchs!

We at IGV strongly believe that peaceful, non-violent activism offers social movements the most power to effect change.Through peaceful protests, we set an example of making our voices heard with dignity, empowered by truth. IGV does not condone intimidation, threats, vandalism, interference with access to a business, or any other lawless actions. If instigators or our opponents attempt to violate our commitment to non-violence, we will try to de-escalate them and will call law enforcement if needed to shut down such unauthorized activity.

We know many of us have very strong feelings about issues and people at this time. If you feel that you may have difficulty remaining nonviolent, please do not attend this activity.

title: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0
description:
For May 11 protest:

Meet in the public lot behind the Flanders Professional Building. It’s in the middle of the block bordered by NW 22nd and 23rd, and NW Everett and Flanders.

Please back into a spot by 1:45 so you’re positioned to pull into the caravan when we leave at 2:00. 

The 5/11 route will have some slow stretches with quite quite a few pauses at lights and intersections. We use these pauses as part of the protest: shout, chant, show your signs, pass out pamphlets or buttons, etc. We do get split up, but we all get back together at the end of these stretches. We’ll talk about traffic and safety and a few tips to keep it all together at 1:45.
The 5/11 PDX Car Caravan Protest will end at the ICE building in S Portland. A Mother’s Day Vigil and Memorial will be held there at 4:00, which is close to our ETA. You are invited to join this additional protest put on by PDX Contra las Deportaciones to protest and remember the victims of the Trump administration’s cruel abductions and deportations.



This a local Indivisible event!

PDX Car Caravan Protest 1.0 was active weekly or more for over a year, 2020-21, and protested racial injustice and police brutality. We are back in version 2.0 as a raucous motorized protest for people who love justice and hate injustice of all varieties. If you are outraged and need to protest but for whatever reason don’t (always)do crowds, standing and marching, roll with us. Keep your foot on the gas. 

More details on bluesky and Facebook: PDX Car Caravan Protest 2.0
accessibility_notes: You arrive and can remain in your own vehicle for the entire protest. We give a short traffic safety orientation and provide a written handout. If you need to remain in your vehicle during the orientation, just let us know so we can make sure you can access the information.

Social Security Wednesdays! Join INDIVISIBLE Chester County and Savesocialsecurity.net to support SSA and fight for a functioning SSA, this administration is trying to cripple.

➡️ ➡️ A core principle behind all of our events is a commitment to nonviolent action. We expect all participants to seek to de-escalate any potential confrontation with those who disagree with us.


The Trump administration is taking a hatchet to Social Security, and the time to speak out is now!

Elon Musk’s so-called Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) is trying to seize Social Security data—not to improve the system, but to spread misinformation and justify deep cuts to the benefits working people have earned. Musk has made it clear: he wants to gut Social Security for older Americans, survivors, and people with disabilities.

Social Security has always been there for us:
✔️ Never missed a payment
✔️ 1 in 3 older Americans depends on it for at least 90% of their income
✔️ Without it, 22 million more adults and children would fall below the poverty line

Instead of cutting Social Security, we should be strengthening it—scrap the cap on the Social Security payroll tax and make billionaires like Musk pay their fair share!

title: Orange County Redistricting Public Comment Training
description:
Learn how to make your voice heard in the redistricting process! This training will prepare community members to effectively participate in upcoming public hearings hosted by the Orange County Redistricting Advisory Committee. You'll learn what redistricting is, why it matters, and how to deliver impactful public comments that advocate for fair and equitable maps. Whether new to public testimony or a seasoned advocate, this training will equip you with the tools and talking points to speak up for your community.

Training will be conducted via Zoom on varying dates and times. Just need to sign up for one.

title: 5/13/2025 Open Volunteer Hours
description:
EIF currently offers open volunteering on Tuesdays from 9 AM to 3 PM. Each shift is an hour long, so sign up for as many as you like!

Our address is 2405 North Shore Drive, and we're operating out of our Volunteer Center. Please drive down North Shore Drive until you see the large Volunteer Center street sign on the left side; you'll park in the gravel lot and enter on the north side of the building.

Please keep in mind that while volunteering, the following are not allowed on the volunteer center floor:

•Dangling jewelry (earrings/necklaces)
•Open-toed shoes
•Tank tops
•Phones
•Food/beverage containers
•Gum

If you have any questions, please reach out to us at volunteer@eifoodbank.org. 

Thanks for volunteering with EIF!
